post_text:
All A-P Students Eat For Free

Effective Monday, September 14, the Aplington-Parkersburg Community School District will begin serving free breakfast and lunch to EVERY student currently enrolled in Aplington-Parkersburg Schools through the USDA Feeding Program. The program includes ALL students, including those learning remotely. This extension runs through December 31 or until funding runs out. Ala carte and other extras are still available to purchase through the student's lunch account after the free meal is provided. This is a magnificent opportunity for our students!

post_text:
Hello Volleyball Parents and Fans!

In anticipation of hosting tomorrow’s tournament, please review the following guidelines:

•Please stay home if you are not feeling well.

•Physical distance from those outside your family cohort.

•Masks are REQUIRED in the gyms, hallways and common areas. Please remember that a properly worn face covering is worn over the mouth and nose.

•A MASK FREE zone will be set up in the music hallway and you are more than welcome to be outside without a mask.

You’ve probably noticed that the players and coaches are doing an excellent job of wearing a face covering on the sidelines. Please respect the desire of all people to remain healthy by doing your part in reducing the transmission of the coronavirus.

We are looking forward to tomorrow’s tournament! GO FALCONS!

post_text:
Just a quick reminder-With Fall sports and camps starting up, please remember that each athlete must have a current sports physical on file with the school. Sports physicals that were completed after July 1, 2019 will now be accepted as current through Dec. 31st, 2020 per Governor Reynolds's amendment. IF your physical was completed PRIOR to July 1, 2019, YOU NEED TO HAVE A NEW PHYSICAL COMPLETED PRIOR TO THE START OF THE FALL SEASON. All others will have until Dec. 31st 2020 to get a new physical completed.

Forms are available in the entryway of the high school or will be available on the website for registration to print.

Varsity Football cheerleading try-outs will be held at the high school Monday July 13th and Tuesday July 14th both days at 12:30pm.

Candidates should wear shorts, an AP shirt and tennis shoes. Please have hair up and remove all jewelry.

Candidates will be taught skills and cheers for their try-out and allowed time to practice before tryouts. The following skills will be taught to demonstrate- toe touch, pike and herky.

Cheer camp is planned the last week of July 27 - 31

In this time of social distancing and with some students in need of quarantine video submissions will be accepted.

Any questions please text Katie Egloff at (319)404-9292 or Kiley Fobian at (319) 240-6673

Aplington-Parkersburg Community Schools will be opening the fitness center once again, Starting July 1st 2020.
-We recommend you wipe down the machine and equipment before and after your workout.
-Continue to practice social distancing, with the cardio machines we must leave one machine open in between patrons.
-There will be a checklist of questions we ask people to answer prior to entering the weight room and be respectful and responsible to the other patrons before entering.
-Please fill out the sign in/out sheet.
-There will be a waiver form that you must sign and leave in the box before entering and working out.

Membership to the fitness center / small gym will be extended through December. New memberships will be required starting January 1, 2021.

Aplington-Parkersburg Elementary would like to invite parents, grandparents, friends and community members to be a guest reader in a classroom during our Read a Million Minutes Community Week March 16-20. Sign up here to Read at Parkersburg Elementary
https://www.signupgenius.com/go/904054CA9A62EA13-parkersburg

Sign up here to Read at Aplington Elementary
https://www.signupgenius.com/go/904054CA9A62EA13-aplington

Share the links and spread the word - we'd love to fill our halls with extra readers during Community Week!
Thank you!
AP Elementary Staff

Aplington-Parkersburg Preschool Sign-Up
2020-2021 School Year

Sign-Up for the 2020-2021 Aplington-Parkersburg Preschool classes will be available online beginning Friday, January 24, 2020 on the Aplington - Parkersburg School website (www.a-pcsd.net). To sign your child up for preschool on the website, select “Schools”, choose “Elementary School”, under “School Information”, then under “Parent Resources” choose “A-P Preschool Sign-up”.

Be sure to Sign-up information will be used for configuration of next year’s preschool classes as well as for sending out further information.

Be advised there is a limit on enrollment for preschool. The district operates preschool programs for children ages 3-1/2 and 4 years of age. (Birth date for the youngest child considered is March 15, 2017. 4-year-olds must be 4 on or before September 15, 2020.)

If you have any questions regarding sign-up, call the Parkersburg Elementary office at 346-2446.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdNR9DbaJ-GrEGzelEDfdCHMKV3-xdyISlHAqf1P5R7DID29A/closedform
